}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10455/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10455/canvas/1/49420ef5-bd52-4650-a3b2-4b3a271996d2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:32:48.317Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In this scene, Reynolds is often seen in single shots, Alma in dirty singles. This difference signifies the power that Reynolds wields, while Alma remains in his shadow.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10455/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:29.145642201834825,32.14592889908225,271.1080848623853,227.22190366972478"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10455/canvas/1/cddf9b14-8105-41c2-a256-8a0468a31b56","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:33:16.351Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds shares these long client histories with the Spanish designer Cristóbal Balenciaga. For instance, the latter made a first communion dress and a wedding gown for the Marquesa de Llanzol (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 156).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10455/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:330.27092889908255,34.91255733944925,274.37643348623857,231.27866972477065"}}}]}]}]}